Software installing  and configuring on Debian

In mc in Option menu change autoindent and using internal editor (on)

mcedit will be defailt text editor for python scripts, or JED - this should every student choose themself.

Eventually Geany can be installed (apt-get install geany), but this is X11-Window application,
so can be more RAM depedent (gets more resources from system), and to use it, student must use Linux machine and access to Galileo with command:
ssh -C root@_galileo_ip_ -X -Y (refer to ssh manual fore more info about tjis 2 options).


